node.text:
Honored to win this years Triple Crown, it was a ton of fun. I wasn’t sure what to expect when I signed up, I just thought I’d be surfing those spots anyways so I might as well give it a go. Then watching everyone pushing their limits on day 1 got me really inspired, and totally changed my mindset. Big days at Haleiwa, Sunset and Pipe are so taxing, but everyone was putting in a ton of effort and time at each venue. The format was a lot of fun and so unique to what we’re used to. It was wild spending so many hours in the water through all the swell we had. Thank you to the community here on the North Shore for sharing the lineups and making this possible. Congrats @rissmoore10 for winning the women’s division, you were ripping!
-
🎶 @ronartisii

node.text:
After injuring my knee last summer I didn’t think it would be possible to surf the Pipe Masters five months after surgery, but I decided to make that my goal and give myself every chance to compete in case there was still a possibility to qualify for the Olympics.  Hopefully this film inspires people to go after their goals.
	⁃	
Thank you to the medical team and physical therapists that made this possible, to my team for their support over the last year, the team @clifbar for supporting me to tell this story, the @wsl for working with us, and every surfer on tour - it’s incredible to see how far everyone is taking the level of surfing in competition. 
	⁃	
#TokyoRising available on @amazonprimevideo Thursday 11/12
🎥 @parallelsea

Europe has always been a really special place for my family.  When we were young our Mom would take my brothers and I to France for the summer and we would spend all of our time looking for our own little sandbars and setting up the best beach days. It never changed when we got older. Excited to share that our @florence_marine_x gear is now available in the UK and Europe.
—
FlorenceMarinex.eu
FlorenceMarinex.co.uk

node.text:
I’ve decided to withdraw from the next two @wsl events in Mexico and Tahiti. This was a really hard decision to make, but I’m not 100% healed from my knee surgery and I’m trying to do the right thing for my future health and goals. The opportunity to surf in Tokyo was once in a lifetime, and a risk I was willing to take. But looking at the rest of the year and talking with my medical team the best step forward is continuing with physical therapy for the next 60 days. I want to make sure there is nothing that keeps me from competing, and surfing the way I want to in the long term. With all that said, I’ll be ready to go for the Pipe Masters and excited to compete! Good luck to everyone still in the World Title race — it’s gonna be an exciting end to the year! Thanks for all of the support 🤙
-
📸 @justinjjung

node.text:
Today was an emotional day, saying good bye to a legend of our sport and someone that has inspired me growing up in Hawaii. 
Seeing the clips and photos of everyone coming together made me sad I couldn’t be there today. My love goes out to the Ho family and everyone in our community. 🎥 @erik_knutson_
